        "short_description": "Crispy, golden fried chicken served with roasted or pan-fried potatoes — a comforting, savory dinner swap that replaces the roast variation with a classic fried preparation.",
        "meal_suggestion": "Season bone-in chicken pieces (or your preferred cuts) with salt, pepper, and a blend of paprika, garlic powder, and a touch of cayenne. Dredge in seasoned flour, dip in beaten egg, then coat with panko or extra flour. Fry in hot oil (175–180°C / 350–360°F) until cooked through and crisp, or shallow-fry in a skillet for a lighter finish. For the potatoes, cut baby potatoes or Yukon golds into halves or wedges, toss with olive oil, salt, pepper, and rosemary, then roast at 200°C (400°F) until golden and tender, or pan-fry until crisp. Serve the fried chicken alongside the potatoes with a simple green salad or steamed vegetables and lemon wedges.",
